Minister of basic education Angie Motshekga gave an update on Thursday on schools' progress on moving to Covid-19 lockdown level 1 restrictions. Motshekga touched on school nutrition plans, bullying and, most importantly, school calendar amendments. She  also paid tribute to teachers  who have been working around the clock to ensure that pupils are kept up to date, even if it means having to teach on weekends. TimesLIVE